# ── Required ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your Gemini API key. Used server-side only by the api/ functions — never
# exposed to the browser. Without this set, all three AI features
# (Thumbnail Analyzer, Viral Topic Finder, Title Optimizer) automatically
# fall back to a built-in deterministic simulator so the app still works
# end-to-end for demos/testing.
GEMINI_API_KEY="your-gemini-api-key-here"

# ── Recommended for production ───────────────────────────────────────────

# Redis credentials for persistent storage of users, thumbnail history,
# and saved topics/titles. Without these, the app uses an in-memory store
# that is wiped on every cold start / deploy — fine for a quick demo, not
# fine for real users.
#
# Easiest setup: from your project directory, run
#   vercel install
# and choose a Redis provider (e.g. Upstash) from the Marketplace. Vercel
# will provision the database and automatically add the matching env vars
# to your project — you will not need to copy/paste these by hand.
#
# If you provision Upstash Redis directly (without the Vercel integration),
# use these names instead — the app checks both:
#   UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL="https://your-instance.upstash.io"
#   UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN="your-upstash-rest-token"
KV_REST_API_URL="https://your-instance.upstash.io"
KV_REST_API_TOKEN="your-upstash-rest-token"
